{"nodes":[{"pos":[12,49],"content":"Compiler Error C2062 | Microsoft Docs","needQuote":false,"needEscape":true,"nodes":[{"content":"Compiler Error C2062 | Microsoft Docs","pos":[0,37]}]},{"pos":[597,617],"content":"Compiler Error C2062","linkify":"Compiler Error C2062","nodes":[{"content":"Compiler Error C2062","pos":[0,20]}]},{"content":"type 'type' unexpected","pos":[618,640]},{"content":"The compiler did not expect a type name.","pos":[647,687]},{"content":"The following sample generates C2062:","pos":[694,731]},{"content":"C2062 can also occur due to the way the compiler handles undefined types in a constructor's parameter list.","pos":[867,974]},{"content":"If the compiler encounters an undefined (misspelled?) type, it assumes the constructor is an expression, and issues C2062.","pos":[975,1097]},{"content":"To resolve, only use defined types in a constructor parameter list.","pos":[1098,1165]}],"content":"---\ntitle: \"Compiler Error C2062 | Microsoft Docs\"\nms.custom: \"\"\nms.date: \"11/04/2016\"\nms.reviewer: \"\"\nms.suite: \"\"\nms.technology: \n  - \"devlang-cpp\"\nms.tgt_pltfrm: \"\"\nms.topic: \"error-reference\"\nf1_keywords: \n  - \"C2062\"\ndev_langs: \n  - \"C++\"\nhelpviewer_keywords: \n  - \"C2062\"\nms.assetid: 6cc98353-2ddf-43ab-88a2-9cc91cdd6033\ncaps.latest.revision: 9\nauthor: \"corob-msft\"\nms.author: \"corob\"\nmanager: \"ghogen\"\ntranslation.priority.ht: \n  - \"cs-cz\"\n  - \"de-de\"\n  - \"es-es\"\n  - \"fr-fr\"\n  - \"it-it\"\n  - \"ja-jp\"\n  - \"ko-kr\"\n  - \"pl-pl\"\n  - \"pt-br\"\n  - \"ru-ru\"\n  - \"tr-tr\"\n  - \"zh-cn\"\n  - \"zh-tw\"\n---\n# Compiler Error C2062\ntype 'type' unexpected  \n  \n The compiler did not expect a type name.  \n  \n The following sample generates C2062:  \n  \n```  \n// C2062.cpp  \n// compile with: /c  \nstruct A {  : int l; };   // C2062  \nstruct B { private: int l; };   // OK  \n```  \n  \n C2062 can also occur due to the way the compiler handles undefined types in a constructor's parameter list. If the compiler encounters an undefined (misspelled?) type, it assumes the constructor is an expression, and issues C2062. To resolve, only use defined types in a constructor parameter list."}